irskaya, E.V., Rybkina, N.L., The brachiopods and biostratigraphy of the Upper Ordovician and Silurian of Tuva (1985) Transactions of the Institute of Geology and Geophysics, Siberian Branch Academy of Sciences of USSR, 635, pp. 1-208. , In Russian; Laurie, J.R., Articulate brachiopods from the Ordovician and Lower Silurian of Tasmania (1991) Association of Australasian Palaeontologists Memoir, 11, pp. 1-106; Li, R., Copper, P., Early Silurian (Llandovery) orthide brachiopods from Anticosti Island, eastern Canada: The O/S extinction event recovery fauna (2006) Special Papers in Palaeontology, 76, pp. 1-71. , pls 1-19; Modzalevskaya, T.L., Popov, L.E., Earliest Silurian articulate brachiopods from central Kazakhstan (1995) Acta Palaeontologica Polonica, 40, pp. 399-426; Nikiforova, O.I., Brachiopods of the Tchasmankalon, Artchalyk and Minkutcher Beds (1978) Trudy Institute Geologi i Geofiziki Sibirskoe Otdelenii Akademia Nauk SSSR, 397, pp. 102-125. , In Russian; Rong. J.-y., Chen, X. Su, Y.-z., Ni, Y.-n., Zhan, R.-b., Chen, T.-e., Fu, L.-p., Li, R.-y. & Fan, J.-x. 2003a. Silurian paleogeography of China. In Landing, E. & Johnson, M. E. (eds) Silurian Lands and Seas, Paleogeography Outside of Laurentia. New York State Museum Bulletin 493, 243-98Rong, J.-y, Zhan, R.-b. & Harper, D. A. T. 2003b. Rhuddanian (Llandovery, Silurian) brachiopod assemblages from the Yangtze Region, South China. INSUGEO Serie Correlacion Geologica 18, 173-8Rong, J.-y., Zhan, R.-b, & Jin, J. 2004. The Late Ordovician and Early Silurian pentameride brachiopod Holorhynchus Kiaer, 1902 from North China. Journal of Paleontology 78, 287-99Rong, J.-Y., Boucot, A.J., Harper, D.A.T., Zhan, R.-B., Neuman, R.B., Global analyses of brachiopod faunas through the Ordovician and Silurian transition: Reducing the role of the Lazarus effect (2006) Canadian Journal of Earth Sciences, 43, pp. 23-39; Rong, J.-Y., Chen, X., Silurian biostratigraphy of China (2003) Biostratigraphy of China, pp. 173-236. , Zhang, W